I'll be completely honest because you should be completely aware of the way a business runs things and how good their food is before ordering. If you care about the whole experience read on, if you're here to find out how good the food is, skip to the third paragraph :)  Now I'll tell you that my first impression from this diner wasn't too good. I clearly stated my cell phone number and my apt number. (another thing is, my lobby door isn't locked so if she would have taken the info down correctly he would have delivered without even having to buzz) but after an hour of waiting I called the diner back to find out where the order was and the "lady" shouts "you didn't give me the apt number!" I said I did, its a part of my address like the building number. I mean, Lady, I know you think I didn't give you the APT number but what you did have to work with was my cell phone number. Why you did not call me when you realized you didn't have the apt number or when you found out the delivery boy was lost, I DO NOT KNOW....Glad I snapped and called after an hour.  However, after heating up the food just a tiny bit in the toaster oven (thank god we have one, the food is in foils or else we would have had to use dishes (totally defeats the purpose of take out on a day you worked a long shift at the office) so we stuck it into the toaster oven for about 10 mins each and ta dah the food was fresh again. It was SOOOOOOO delicious. They forgot to add ketchup and mayo but its okay! We had time to grab that from the fridge while the food was heating.  This is good quality food. I will be ordering again and double checking that she has my apt number AND understands she can call if there is any problem :)  Only three stars because waiting an hour for your food, being told you messed up when you didn't and finding out your delivery boy is lost with your cold food is a tad disturbing but hey 5 stars for the food!
